course_aims:
This course aims to develop entrepreneurs and entrepreneurship by introducing students to the theory, practice and research needed to start and grow new ventures, by:

exploring the key concepts of entrepreneurship to navigate uncertainty & generate testable assumptions;

designing innovative business models to both deliver and capture value;

practice in developing & presenting new business ideas and analysing existing & emerging entrepreneurial firms;

creating competitive advantage through venture formation, market analysis and entrepreneurial strategy; and

building confidence in students so to act on their entrepreneurial ambitions.
